default&#xa0;
defaultYou are driving in the left-hand lane on a three-lane dual carriageway subject to the national speed limit.  It is a windy day 
defaultand you are towing a small trailer which begins to snake. Ahead, in the centre lane, there is a slower moving motorcyclist that you intend to overtake.
defaultYou move into the center lane and the motorcyclist moves into the left-hand lane.  
defaultAfter leaving the du
defaultal carriageway you approach a half barrier level crossing. Flashing red lights are showing. Two trains pass before the barrier goes up. Further along the road you stop in heavy traffic. The car behind runs into the back of you. The driver is displaying a h
defaultelp pennant. You are carrying a red warning triangle.
default&#xa0;
defaultWhat should you do after seeing the first train pass?
default&#xa0;
defaultWait for the lights to go off and the barriers open
default&#xa0;
defaultLook left, right, left, and proceeds if clear
default&#xa0;
defaultLook right, left, right, and proceed if clear
default&#xa0;
defaultWait for the amber light and zigzag around the barriers
